	heroObjectPosition={`center top`}
	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If you're a first responder, the Father's Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> Police officer, firefighter, EMT, paramedic, dispatcher — you carry what most people will never see: the calls that don't leave, the bodies you couldn't save, the hypervigilance that follows you home. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free on your phone — and it reveals God as a <em>Father</em> from beginning to end. Whether you searched "Bible verses for first responders," "verses for police officers," "firefighter encouragement," or "Scripture for EMS," the answer starts in one place: the strength you need isn't being unbreakable. It's a Father who runs toward you, sees what you've seen, and stays.`}
	keyTakeaway={`The answer to a first responder's pain is not unbreakable toughness. It's a Father who runs toward you the way you run toward everyone else — who sees what you've seen, and stays.`}
	painsHeading={`The weight first responders carry`}
	painsIntroHtml={`If you feel exhausted, on edge, or like you have to be the strong one no matter what, you are not weak and you are not alone. The people who run toward danger carry a hidden cost — and the numbers say it out loud.`}
	painStats={[
		{ value: `30%`, label: `of first responders develop behavioral health conditions like depression and PTSD, vs. 20% in the general population (SAMHSA)` },
		{ value: `Up to 1 in 3`, label: `police officers and firefighters experience symptoms of PTSD over the course of a career (SAMHSA)` },
		{ value: `More likely to die by suicide than in the line of duty`, label: `firefighters and police officers, according to a national review (Ruderman Family Foundation, 2018)` },
		{ value: `Hundreds`, label: `of critical, traumatic incidents a typical EMS provider may witness over a career (Journal of Emergency Medical Services)` },
		{ value: `Higher rates`, label: `of depression and PTSD among 911 dispatchers, who relive callers' worst moments without ever seeing the scene (SAMHSA)` },
		{ value: `Chronic sleep loss`, label: `from rotating and overnight shift work raises the risk of fatigue, depression, and burnout among emergency workers (CDC / NIOSH)` },
