	aFatherHeading={`A Father for first responders`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here's what almost no one tells you in this line of work: the answer to what you carry isn't becoming more unbreakable. It's a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a perfect, holy Father who runs toward you the way you run toward everyone else, and who already loves you, today, exactly as you are.</p><p>You were not made to be the one who never breaks. You were made to be held. And the One who made you doesn't need you to carry it alone or hide the weight to keep His respect. He calls you His beloved child — not the iron-jawed version, not the one who has it all together, but <em>you</em>, after the worst shift, with everything you've seen.</p><p>So before you're an officer, a firefighter, a medic, a dispatcher — you are His. Your heavenly Father wants to be the steady presence in the long nights, the One who says: I saw that call, I was there, you don't have to be the strong one with Me. Come to Me, and I'll carry you the way you've carried everyone else.</p>`}
