	voiceIntroHtml={`Nine Bible verses for first responders in the Father's Heart Bible™ — each one a word from your perfect Father, straight to the weight you carry. Tap any reference to read and listen free.`}
	verses={[
		{ ref: `Psalm 91:1-2`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 91, text: `Whoever dwells in the shelter of your Father will rest in His shadow. Say of Him: He is my refuge and my fortress, my Father, in whom I trust.`, note: `You're the shelter everyone runs to — but your Father is the shelter you can run to, on and off the clock.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 41:10`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 41, text: `Do not fear, for I am with you; do not be dismayed, for I am your Father. I will strengthen you, I will help you, I will hold you up with My righteous right hand.`, note: `You don't have to manufacture courage alone — your Father is holding you up through every call.` },
		{ ref: `Joshua 1:9`, slug: `joshua`, ch: 1, text: `Have I not commanded you? Be strong and courageous. Do not be afraid; do not be discouraged, for your Father is with you wherever you go.`, note: `Into the wreck, into the fire, into the scene — wherever you're sent, your Father goes with you.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 46:1`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 46, text: `Your Father is your refuge and strength, an ever-present help in trouble.`, note: `When you're the help everyone calls, remember there's a Father who is your ever-present help.` },
		{ ref: `Matthew 11:28`, slug: `matthew`, ch: 11, text: `Come to Me, all you who are weary and burdened, and I will give you rest, says your Father.`, note: `After the shift that drained everything, you have a Father whose whole offer is rest.` },
		{ ref: `Philippians 4:6-7`, slug: `philippians`, ch: 4, text: `Do not be anxious about anything, but in everything, by prayer, bring your requests to your Father — and His peace, beyond all understanding, will guard your heart and mind.`, note: `Hand the hypervigilance to your Father, and let His peace stand watch over your heart and mind tonight.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 34:18`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 34, text: `Your Father is close to the brokenhearted and saves those who are crushed in spirit.`, note: `The calls that break your heart don't push Him away — they draw your Father near.` },
		{ ref: `John 15:13`, slug: `john`, ch: 15, text: `Greater love has no one than this: to lay down one's life for one's friends, says your Father.`, note: `The love you live out every shift is the very love your Father has for you — He laid His own life down.` },
		{ ref: `Deuteronomy 31:8`, slug: `deuteronomy`, ch: 31, text: `Your Father Himself goes before you and will be with you; He will never leave you nor forsake you. Do not be afraid; do not be discouraged.`, note: `He's already on scene before you arrive, and He stays long after the call clears — He never leaves.` },
	]}
