	voicesHeading={`The Father's heart, in their words`}
	voicesIntroHtml={`You run toward what everyone else runs from, and carry calls no one should have to carry. The truth beneath every verse here, that God is before anything else a Father, is the one these voices gave their lives to:`}
	voices={[
		{ quote: `There is heaven in the depth of that word — Father.`, name: `Charles Spurgeon`, role: `the “Prince of Preachers”`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/e48a128da123135241be9c95cf35b37498d94ea5-500x617.jpg` },
		{ quote: `Answered prayer is the interchange of love between the Father and His child.`, name: `Andrew Murray`, role: `who taught a generation to live as the Father's children`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/133bc45cfa954cf1ae99b7afac5954eca764ed70-500x830.jpg` },
		{ quote: `God tenderly invites us to believe that He is our true Father and we are His true children.`, name: `Martin Luther`, role: `the Reformer, on the opening words of the Lord's Prayer`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/b205722e3e040337b10b11b66e159abd8623472e-500x791.jpg` },
	]}
	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; Charles Spurgeon, Andrew Murray, and Martin Luther (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You might not feel different the first time you read it. That's okay. The Father's love isn't an adrenaline hit — it's a foundation, and foundations get built quietly, one shift at a time. Every verse you take in is your Father planting something in you that the calls can't uproot.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I saw that call. I was on that scene before you arrived, and I was still there when you couldn't save them. I know what your eyes have taken in and what you've never said out loud. And I want you to hear Me over all of it: you are Mine, and I love you right now — not the unbreakable you, not the one who has it together. You.</p><p>You don't have to be the strong one with Me. You don't have to swallow it or carry it alone. I run toward you the way you run toward everyone else — come to Me weary, come to Me broken, come to Me exactly as the shift left you. I'll strengthen you, I'll quiet your heart, and I'll never leave your side. I'm your Father, I see you, and I'm not going anywhere."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for first responders`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for these first responders — every officer, firefighter, medic, and dispatcher who runs toward what the rest of us flee. Watch over them on every call. Put Your shield around them as they walk into danger, and bring them home safe to the people who love them.</p><p>Father, You see what they carry that no one else sees — the calls that replay, the faces they couldn't save, the weight they're told to hide. Be their refuge when the shift ends. Quiet their hypervigilance, give their bodies real rest through broken sleep and long nights, and draw near to every heart that is breaking under what it has witnessed. Guard them from despair, and remind them they were never meant to be the strong one alone.</p><p>Strengthen their families who wait and worry, and bind them together in Your love. Let every one of these responders know You as their Father — not a distant chaplain's line, but the One who runs toward them and stays. May they wake each day knowing they are seen, held, and deeply loved by their heavenly Father.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
