	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for first responders?`, answer: `Psalm 91:1-2 (your Father is your refuge and fortress), Isaiah 41:10 (do not fear, I will strengthen and hold you), Joshua 1:9 (be strong and courageous, your Father is with you wherever you go), Psalm 46:1 (an ever-present help in trouble), Matthew 11:28 (come to Me and I will give you rest), Psalm 34:18 (close to the brokenhearted), and Deuteronomy 31:8 (He goes before you and will never leave you) all speak straight to what first responders carry. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about the trauma and stress of emergency work?`, answer: `Scripture takes your pain seriously and offers a real place to put it. Psalm 34:18 says your Father is close to the brokenhearted and saves those crushed in spirit, and Philippians 4:6-7 says bring your anxiety to God and His peace will guard your heart and mind. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as a Father you can actually hand the weight of the worst calls to — read those passages free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Are there Bible verses for police officers and firefighters?`, answer: `Yes. Joshua 1:9 commands you to be strong and courageous because your Father is with you wherever you go, Isaiah 41:10 promises He will strengthen and uphold you, and John 15:13 honors the love that lays down its life for others — the very love your Father has for you. For the officer or firefighter walking into danger, these are the Father's own words. Read and listen free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What Scripture helps with the exhaustion and sleep loss of shift work?`, answer: `Matthew 11:28 is the Father's direct invitation: come to Me, all you who are weary and burdened, and I will give you rest. Psalm 91 pictures Him as the shelter you can rest in after the shift, and Philippians 4:6-7 offers peace that guards your mind through broken sleep. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you meet a Father whose promise to the worn-down is rest — read or listen free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free Bible with audio for first responders on shift?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on your phone and read or hear any book — perfect for listening in the rig, on a quiet stretch of patrol, or when the calls replay late at night.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different for first responders?`, answer: `It's the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so instead of one more voice telling you to be tough, you meet the One who runs toward you and stays. For a responder under constant pressure to be the strong one, that reframes everything: you come to the Bible as a loved child first, not a hero who has to hold it all together. Read and listen free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `How can I start reading the Bible as a first responder?`, answer: `Start small and start free. Open fathersheartbible.com/read, pick a Psalm or a short book, and listen to the audio between calls or after a shift. Try a verse a day — Psalm 91, Isaiah 41, or Matthew 11 are great places to begin. Our how-to-pray guide and verses-by-topic pages can help you find words for whatever the job has left you carrying.` },
	]}
